<summary><strong>file_io_large</strong> — Performing file I/O operations on a large file</summary>

This task reads the same deterministic fixture in every language and validates the workload with a printed checksum/result. This focuses on streaming file I/O, text parsing overhead, buffered reading behavior, and the runtime cost of turning a large raw file into usable numeric values.

##### PHP

```php
<?php
function run_file_io_large(string $size, string $fixturesRoot): void {
  $path = $fixturesRoot . "/generated/file_io/{$size}.txt";
  $handle = fopen($path, 'r');
  $total = 0;
  while (($line = fgets($handle)) !== false) {
    $total += intval(trim($line));
  }
  fclose($handle);
  echo $total . PHP_EOL;
}
```

##### Python

```python
